Package gui

Class Graph

  • java.lang.Object
    • gui.Graph
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    JSONString
    public final class Graph
extends java.lang.Object
implements JSONString
    An instance contains HashSets of Edges and Nodes that make up the graph.

    Graphs are either randomly generated from a seed or loaded from a file.

        public boolean isIntersection()
        Return true iff there is any intersection of the lines drawn by the edges in edges. Used for GUI intersection detection, not useful outside of the GUI context.
        Has nothing to say about the non-GUI version of the graph.
        Students: not Useful for you.

      • getAIntersection

        public EdgeData[] getAIntersection()
        Return a 2x1 array of edges that have lines that intersect.
        If no two edges intersect, return null. Used for GUI intersection detection, not useful outside of the GUI context.
        Has nothing to say about the non-GUI version of the board.
        Students: Not useful
